dies%20and%20stayed%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmall%20group%26quot%3B%20of%20Arabs%20from%20Kuwait%2C%20biographer%20Richard%20Miniter%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKSM's%20limited%20and%20negative%20experience%20in%20the%20United%20States%20--%20which%20included%20a%20brief%20jail%20stay%20because%20of%20unpaid%20bills%20--%20almost%20certainly%20helped%20propel%20him%20on%20his%20path%20to%20becoming%20a%20terrorist%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20US%20intelligence%20summary%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201987%2C%20he%20traveled%20to%20Afghanistan%20and%20fought%20alongside%20mujahedeen%20rebels%20against%20the%20Soviet%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20stayed%20in%20Afghanistan%20until%201992%2C%20and%20then%20headed%20to%20Bosnia%20and%20Herzegovina%20to%20fight%20with%20Muslim%20fighters%20against%20the%20Serbs%2C%20according%20to%20the%209%2F11%20Commission%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20not%20until%20a%20botched%201995%20plot%20to%20blow%20up%20US%20airliners%20over%20the%20Pacific%2C%20known%20as%20Operation%20Bojinka%2C%20that%20he%20achieved%20notoriety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20earlier%20helped%20finance%20the%201993%20World%20Trade%20Center%20bombing%20hatched%20by%20his%20nephew%20Ramzi%20Youssef%20that%20killed%20six%20people%20and%20wounded%20more%20than%201%2C000%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohammed%20fought%20alongside%20Bin%20Laden%20in%20Afghanistan%20in%20the%20late%201980s%2C%20but%20they%20did%20not%20forge%20a%20close%20relationship%20until%2010%20years%20later%2C%20at%20which%20point%20Mohammed%20began%20plotting%20what%20would%20later%20become%20the%20September%2011%2C%202001%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBin%20Laden%20realized%20that%20this%20difficult%20little%20man%20was%20absolutely%20essential%20for%20turning%20AQ%20into%20the%20kind%20of%20organization%20he%20wanted%2C%26quot%3B%20Miniter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohammed%20then%20had%20a%20hand%20in%20nearly%20every%20single%20Al-Qaeda%20plot%20until%20his%20arrest.%20But%20experts%20say%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20that%20one%20man%20alone%20was%20at%20the%20center%20of%20all%20these%20terror%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20obviously%20a%20smart%20guy%2C%20but%20he's%20not%20a%20genius...%20He%20didn't%20do%20the%20impossible%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Terry%20McDermott%2C%20co-author%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Hunt%20for%20KSM.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20what%20is%20known%20about%20Mohammed%20comes%20from%20interrogation%20transcripts%20released%20by%20the%20Pentagon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20known%20to%20have%20been%20waterboarded%20183%20times%20during%20his%20years%20in%20US%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERights%20groups%20denounce%20the%20simulated%20drowning%20technique%20as%20torture%2C%20and%20it%20later%20led%20to%20years%20of%20delays%20in%20his%20trial%20due%20to%20legal%20manoeuverings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20reported%20confessions%2C%20Mohammed%20claimed%20to%20be%20the%20%26quot%3Bmilitary%20operational%20commander%26quot%3B%20for%20all%20Al-Qaeda%20foreign%20operations%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20making%20myself%20a%20hero.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20looking%20to%20be%20a%20martyr%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20a%20hearing%20at%20Guantanamo%20in%20June%202008%2C%20the%20first%20time%20he%20had%20appeared%20in%20public%20since%20his%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722563460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2F1jmfn9g_khalid-sheikh-mohammed_625x300_02_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-is-khalid-sheikh-mohammed-pakistani-terrorist-behind-9-11-attacks-6244505%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Khalid%20Sheikh%20Mohammed%2C%2