d-to-rejoin-soon%2Farticleshow%2F112209768.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Is%20Vadim%20Krasikov%2C%20The%20Assassin%20Freed%20In%20Russian%20Prisoner%20Swap%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EVadim%20Krasikov%2C%20a%20Russian%20freed%20from%20jail%20in%20Germany%20on%20Friday%20in%20a%20prisoner%20swap%20between%20Moscow%20and%20the%20West%2C%20was%20convicted%20of%20the%20murder%20in%202019%20of%20a%20former%20Chechen%20militant%20as%20he%20walked%20in%20broad%20daylight%20in%20a%20park%20in%20central%20Berlin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20brazenness%20of%20the%20murder%2C%20committed%20a%20few%20minutes'%20walk%20from%20parliament%20and%20the%20office%20of%20then-chancellor%20Angela%20Merkel%2C%20sparked%20outrage%20in%20Germany%20that%20has%20complicated%20attempts%20to%20swap%20him%20for%20the%20growing%20list%20of%20political%20prisoners%20the%20West%20would%20like%20freed%20from%20Russian%20jails.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20called%20the%20killing%20of%20Georgian%20citizen%20Zelimkhan%20Khangoshvili%20%26quot%3Bstate%20terrorism%26quot%3B%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20order%20had%20almost%20certainly%20come%20from%20Putin%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20evidence%20he%20cited%20for%20Russian%20state%20involvement%20were%20his%20official%20Russian%20papers%20containing%20a%20false%20identity%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20Russian%20law%20empowered%20Putin%20to%20order%20the%20murder%20of%20state%20enemies%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20shots%20fired%20from%20a%20Glock%20pistol%20on%20a%20sunny%20August%20day%20were%20deemed%20murder%20%26quot%3Bwith%20especially%20serious%20aggravating%20circumstances%26quot%3B%20-%20the%20most%20serious%20conviction%20possible%20under%20German%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParticularly%20aggravating%20was%20the%20fact%20that%20Khangoshvili%20had%20long%20forsworn%20any%20violent%20struggle%20for%20Chechen%20independence%2C%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20was%20not%20an%20act%20of%20self-defence%20by%20Russia.%20This%20was%20and%20is%20nothing%20other%20than%20state%20terrorism%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFour%20children%20lost%20their%20father%2C%20two%20siblings%20their%20brother.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrasikov%20was%20born%20in%20Kazakhstan%2C%20then%20part%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20in%201965%2C%20and%20police%20mugshots%20show%20him%20with%20deep%2C%20narrow-set%20eyes%20and%20a%20mournful%20expression.%20He%20worked%20for%20Russia's%20FSB%20state%20security%20service%2C%20where%2C%20according%20to%20open%20source%20investigators%20Bellingcat%2C%20he%20became%20a%20specialist%20assassin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrasikov's%20conviction%20in%20December%202021%20triggered%20the%20expulsion%20of%20two%20of%20the%20101%20diplomats%20then%20serving%20in%20Russia's%20giant%20Berlin%20embassy.%20Their%20number%20has%20been%20reduced%20by%20another%2050%20since%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20entered%20Germany%20via%20France%20with%20false%20papers%20under%20the%20name%20Vadim%20Sokolov.%20He%20was%20arrested%20minutes%20after%20cycling%20up%20behind%20Khangoshvili%20and%20shooting%20him%20dead%3B%20passers-by%20spotted%20him%20changing%20his%20clothes%2C%20shaving%20off%20his%20beard%20and%20dumping%20his%20bicycle%20in%20a%20pond%2C%20and%20alerted%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Krasikov%20pleaded%20innocent%20and%20maintained%20he%20was%20genuinely%20Sokolov%2C%20a%20St%20Petersburg%20construction%20engineer%20visiting%20Berlin%20as%20a%20tourist%2C%20Putin%20has%20implicitly%20acknowledged%20his%20identity%20and%20profession.%20Last%20year%2C%20without%20naming%20Krasikov%2C%20he%20spoke%20of%20his%20desire%20to%20secure%20the%20release%20of%20someone%20who%20had%20%26quot%3Beliminated%20a%20bandit%20in%20one%20of%20the%20European%20capitals%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20identified%20Krasikov%20with%20the%20help%20of%20Ukraine's%20security%20services%2C%20who%20spotted%20footage%20of%20a%20man%20with%20identical%20tattoos%20-%20seemingly%20of%20a%20demon%20wearing%20a%20crown%20and%20a%20snake%20-%20at%20his%20second%20marriage%2C%20to%20a%20woman%20from%20the%20Ukrainian%20city%20of%20Kharkiv%20in%202010.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20his%20trial%2C%20he%20made%20a%20show%20of%20not%20recognising%20the%20court%2C%20often%20removing%20the%20headset%20relaying%20the%20interpretation%20when%20witnesses%20against%20him%20were%20heard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Germany%2C%20releasing%20him%20is%20legally%20complex%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20seriousness%20of%20the%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpecialists%20have%20suggested%20that%20he%20could%20be%20released%20under%20a%20theoretical%20agreement%20that%20he%20serve%20his%20sentence%20in%20Russia%2C%20even%20if%20the%20Kremlin%20then%20chose%20to%20renege%20on%20this.%20Alternatively%2C%20prosecutors%20could%20state%20that%20they%20no%20longer%20wish%20to%20see%20his%20sentence%20enforced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1722561000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-08%2F4mdgonmo_vadim-krasikov_625x300_02_August_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-is-vadim-krasikov-the-assassin-freed-in-russian-prison-swap-6244346%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vadim%20Krasikov%2C%20a%20Russian%20freed%20from%20jail%20in%20Germany%20on%20Friday%20in%20a%20prisoner%20swap%20between%20Moscow%20and%20the%20West%2C%20was%20convicted%20of%20the%20murder%20in%202019%20of%20a%20former%20Chechen%20militant%20as%20he%20walked%20in%20broad%20daylight%20in%20a%20park%20in%20central%20Berlin.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworl